<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3974.1.5>
    dc:creator "Asiain, Julieta; Márquez, Juan; Irmler, Urlich" ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "New national and state records of Neotropical Staphylinidae (Insecta: Coleoptera)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.238933>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.238936>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.238932>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.238934> .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.238933>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Geographic distribution (as individual tracks) of: A. Holotrochus arcuatus (gray squares), Scaphidium theni (black starts) and Platydracus apicipennis (gray circles). B. Eleusis pallidipennis (gray circles) and Holotrochus politus (gray squares)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/238933/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.238936>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Geographic distribution (as individual tracks) of: A. Lispinus paratardus (white circles) and Nacaeus opacus (black circles). B. Platydracus fulvomaculatus (gray circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/238936/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.238932>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Geographic distribution (as individual tracks) of: A. Eleusis bicolor (gray circles). B. Eleusis insignis (white triangles) and Belonuchus bidens (gray circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/238932/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.238934>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Geographic distribution (as individual tracks) of: A. Leptochirus cephalotes (gray circles) and Nacaeus honduranus (black squares). B. Leptochirus edax (gray circles) and Holotrochus rufopygus (gray starts)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/238934/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

